{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 1013 (PR #3422) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3422.","id":"vf_1f23f794066f61da","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1013: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $h_3(k)$ be the minimal $n$ such that there exists a triangle-free graph on $n$ vertices with chromatic number $k$. Find an asymptotic for $h_3(k)$, and also prove\\[\\lim_{k\\to \\infty}\\frac{h_3(k+1)}{h_3(k)}=1.\\] Current best: It is known that\\[\\frac{\\log k}{\\log\\log k}k^2 \\ll h_3(k) \\ll (\\log k)k^2.\\]The lower bound is due to Graver and Yackel \\cite{GrYa68}, the upper bound follows from Shearer's upper bound for $R(3,k)$ (see [165]). The function $h_r(k)$ for $r\\geq 4$ is the subject of [920]. Prize: no. OEIS: A292528. Tags: graph theory.","id":"vf_930b2fa51f57df3b","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1013.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_1f23f794066f61da","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:1013","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_1f23f794066f61da","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"vf_930b2fa51f57df3b","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_930b2fa51f57df3b","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:1013","trust":"signed"}],"external_refe